<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,310,401,427]" box="[189,310,401,427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,401,427]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="18" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,401,427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,447,580]" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">
Having simple fore tarsus, the new species is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Curran, 1924" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1924" box="[885,1278,447,474]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nectarophagus">
<emphasis box="[885,1100,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">H. nectarophagus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Curran C. H." box="[1114,1278,448,474]" pageId="2" pageNumber="18" pagination="212 - 232" refId="ref11188" refString="Curran C. H. 1924. The Dolichopodidae of South Africa. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 10 (4): 212 - 232." type="journal article" year="1924">Curran, 1924</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differing distinctly in male mid and hind femora each with ventral row of erect cilia, about as long as diameter of femur. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1924" box="[273,607,518,544]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nectarophagus">
<emphasis box="[273,607,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="18">Hercostomus nectarophagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males have no long ventral cilia on femora (
<bibRefCitation author="Grichanov I. Ya." box="[1136,1333,518,544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="18" pagination="7 - 44" refId="ref11215" refString="Grichanov I. Ya. 1999. Afrotropical species of the genus Hercostomus Loew (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). International Journal of Dipterological Research 10 (1): 7 - 44." type="journal article" year="1999">Grichanov 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The hypopygia are rather species-specific in the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
