<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="20" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,288,938,964]" box="[189,288,938,964]" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,288,938,964]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,288,938,964]" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Ecology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,988,1364]" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">
The Brandberg Massif is an isolated mountain range in western 
<collectingCountry box="[971,1072,988,1014]" name="Namibia" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Namibia</collectingCountry>
on the eastern edge of the Namib Desert, located in the Nama Karoo Biome. The 
<typeStatus box="[858,909,1028,1054]" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
locality “Mason Shelter” (1800– 
<quantity box="[1307,1399,1027,1054]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" unit="m" value="1750.0">1750 m</quantity>
a.s.l.) is a more or less flat open plain, dissected by some small riverbeds and fringed by rocky hills with huge boulders and rock slabs. It contains some single trees of 
<taxonomicName authority="Engl." authorityName="Engl." box="[899,1192,1105,1131]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="hereroensis">
<emphasis box="[899,1121,1105,1131]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Acacia hereroensis</emphasis>
Engl.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1202,1398,1106,1131]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="sycomorus">
<emphasis box="[1202,1398,1106,1131]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Ficus sycomorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Engl.) R. Fern. &amp; A. Fern." authorityName="R. Fern. &amp; A. Fern." baseAuthorityName="Engl." box="[275,836,1144,1171]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Ozoroa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crassinervia">
<emphasis box="[275,516,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Ozoroa crassinervia</emphasis>
(Engl.) R.Fern. &amp; A.Fern.
</taxonomicName>
, abundant small trees of 
<taxonomicName authority="Engl." authorityName="Engl." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Burseraceae" genus="Commiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxicola">
<emphasis box="[1137,1399,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Commiphora saxicola</emphasis>
Engl.
</taxonomicName>
and scattered individuals of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Garcke) K. Schum." authorityName="K. Schum." baseAuthorityName="Garcke" box="[616,1130,1183,1210]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sterculia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="quinqueloba">
<emphasis box="[616,880,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Sterculia quinqueloba</emphasis>
(Garcke) K.Schum.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1353,1183,1209]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Galenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis box="[1147,1353,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Galenia africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authority="S. Moore" authorityName="S. Moore" authorityYear="1904" box="[189,548,1221,1248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Eriocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dinteri">
<emphasis box="[189,434,1221,1247]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Eriocephalus dinteri</emphasis>
S.Moore
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[612,881,1221,1247]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Cyphostemma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="currorii">
<emphasis box="[612,881,1221,1247]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Cyphostemma currorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hook.f.) Desc. at the southern margin of the plain. In addition, low shrubs of 
<taxonomicName box="[642,728,1260,1286]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Salsola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[642,728,1260,1286]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Salsola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. are evenly dispersed throughout (
<bibRefCitation author="Koch F." box="[1190,1330,1260,1287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" pagination="115 - 123" refId="ref11592" refString="Koch F. 2006. A contribution to the sawfly fauna of the Brandberg Massif in Namibia (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Argidae, Tenthredinidae). Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 56 (1): 115 - 123. Available from: https: // www. contributions-to-entomology. org / article / view / 1654 / 1653 [accessed 23 Feb. 2020]." type="journal article" year="2006">Koch 2006</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2020" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,531,1299,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandbergensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,531,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">Hercostomus brandbergensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[538,629,1300,1326]" pageId="4" pageNumber="20" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<typeStatus box="[635,686,1300,1326]" pageId="4" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected by Malaise trap installed in one of the riverbeds.
</paragraph>
